  "event_preview": "Albert Park Circuit is measured at 5.278 km (3.280 mi) and hosts FIA Formula 2 as a support series during the Australian Grand Prix weekend. The layout's combination of fast chicanes, a long Lakeside Drive section, and heavy braking zones rewards clean, disciplined driving - crucial for F2 cars with their spec tyres and limited aerodynamic adjustability. Tyre management and overtaking through Turn 3 are key strategic factors across the sprint and feature race formats. The official F2 lap record at Albert Park is 1:28.694, set by Dennis Hauger driving for MP Motorsport in 2024.",
